---
import Layout from '@/components/chrome/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Terms — The STR Ledger"
  description="Terms of use for thestrledger.com workbooks and PDFs."
  path="/terms"
>
  <section class="bg-parchment">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 pt-12 pb-9">
      <p class="label text-gold-deep">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 font-serif text-h1 text-navy leading-tight">
        Terms<span class="period-gold">.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lead text-ink-2">
        The short version: buy a workbook, use it for your portfolio, don't resell it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-parchment-light border-t border-rule">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-9 prose">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-h2 text-navy">License</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-body text-ink-2 leading-snug">
        Each workbook purchase grants a single-operator license. You may use the workbook for your own STR portfolio, including unlimited properties owned or managed by you. You may not resell, redistribute, or sublicense the file. PM companies and coaches: see Wholesale below.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-7 font-serif text-h2 text-navy">Refunds</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-body text-ink-2 leading-snug">
        14-day no-questions refund window on every workbook. Email <a href="mailto:hello@thestrledger.com" class="font-mono">hello@thestrledger.com</a> with your SKU.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-7 font-serif text-h2 text-navy">No tax / legal advice</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-body text-ink-2 leading-snug">
        The workbooks compute numbers from your inputs. They are not tax, legal, or financial advice. Consult a CPA before filing.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-7 font-serif text-h2 text-navy">Wholesale</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-body text-ink-2 leading-snug">
        Coaches, courses, PM companies licensing workbooks for clients: email us. We do reasonable bulk pricing.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-7 text-caption text-ink-3 italic">
        This stub is a placeholder. Full terms in development.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
